{{Wide image|Columbia River Slough (small).jpg|2028px|Map of the Columbia Slough's route through Fairview, Gresham, and Portland. The slough begins at Fairview Lake (right) and flows generally west to its confluence with the Willamette River (left). The route has been artificially straightened in this image by reorienting each panel. The compass rose marks north for each. [[:Image:Columbia River Slough (medium).png|(Zoom in)]]}}
